President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals for key administration posts. Philip Mudd was nominated for Under Secretary for Intelligence and Analysis at the Department of Homeland Security. Kurt Campbell was nominated for Assistant Secretary for East Asian and Pacific Affairs at the State Department. Eric P. Schwartz was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Population, Refugees and Migration at the State Department. Edward M. Avalos was nominated for Under Secretary for Marketing and Regulatory Programs at the Department of Agriculture. These individuals bring extensive experience and expertise to their respective roles and are expected to meet the expectations of the American people.